      "source": [
        "# 🚀 Mickey Jagger - LivePortrait Backend (GPU)\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook sets up the **Mickey Jagger** real-time AI avatar backend using **LivePortrait** with GPU acceleration.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Runtime:** GPU (T4 or better recommended)\n",
        "\n",
        "---"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 1. Install Dependencies"
      ],
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "!pip install fastapi uvicorn python-multipart websockets pillow numpy\n",
        "!pip install torch torchvision --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu121\n",
        "!pip install insightface opencv-python"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 2. Clone Repository"
      ],
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "!git clone https://github.com/KwaiVGI/LivePortrait.git\n",
        "%cd LivePortrait\n",
        "\n",
        "# Initialize submodules\n",
        "!git submodule update --init --recursive"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 3. Download Model Weights"
      ],
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "%cd backend\n",
        "!python download_models.py"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 4. Start Backend Server"
      ],
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "from google.colab import userdata\n",
        "\n",
        "# Install ngrok for public URL\n",
        "!pip install pyngrok\n",
        "\n",
        "from pyngrok import ngrok\n",
        "\n",
        "# Set your ngrok token (get free from https://ngrok.com)\n",
        "# ngrok.set_auth_token('YOUR_TOKEN_HERE')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Create public URL\n",
        "public_url = ngrok.connect(8000)\",
        "print(f'Public URL: {public_url}')\n",
        "\n",
        "# Start server in background\n",
        "import subprocess\n",
        "subprocess.Popen(['uvicorn', 'main:app', '--host', '0.0.0.0', '--port', '8000'], \n",
        "                 stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL, stderr=subprocess.DEVNULL)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## 5. Verify Backend is Running"
      ],
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "import requests\n",
        "\n",
        "try:\n",
        "    response = requests.get('http://localhost:8000/health')\n",
        "    print('✅ Backend is healthy!')\n",
        "    print(response.json())\n",
        "except Exception as e:\n",
        "    print(f'❌ Error: {e}')"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## 📱 Connect Frontend\n",
        "\n",
        "Now update your frontend's `.env.production`:\n",
        "\n",
        "```env\n",
        "NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://your-ngrok-url.ngrok.io\n",
        "NEXT_PUBLIC_WS_URL=https://your-ngrok-url.ngrok.io\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "**Public URL:** " + str(public_url)
      ]
    }
